  "chunk_index": 40,
  "summary": "Following Monsieur Lemont's update to the Earl of Carrington, Bunder expresses disdain for Lemont's appearance. As Virginia Rue prepares for bed, she encounters Chief Inspector Batter leaving through a side door. Virginia questions Batter regarding Lemont's claim that Hiram Fisk is an American detective, which Batter confirms. Disturbed by this information, Virginia retires to her room to reflect on Anthony's previous words.\n\nAt 1:30 a.m., Packard taps on Virginia's window. Acting on behalf of \"the master,\" Packard delivers a note from Anthony stating that he is in danger and attempting to escape. To avoid the detectives stationed near the conference room, Packard instructs Virginia to exit through the side door, where he is waiting with a car. Virginia changes into a yellow sweater and cap, leaves a note for Bunder on a needle cushion, and slips out of the villa.\n\nIn a flashback to Tuesday, October 13, at 10 a.m., Anthony Ked visits Baron Lothrop Loyd at the Hotel Harijgi. Accompanied by a suspicious Captain Andrassy, Anthony proposes a business deal involving supply and demand, cryptically offering to provide a \"prince\" to serve as the backbone for the Baron's political plans. Anthony invites the Baron and Captain Andrassy to the Chimney House at 9 p.m. for further discussion. Afterward, Anthony travels to London to seek an urgent meeting with Mr. Issakov. After mentioning the Chimney House to a military aide, Anthony is granted an immediate audience with Mr. Issakov.",
